f Creation Is a Gift both contributes to the ongoing debate on the gift and provides a fresh philosophical and theological consideration of the environmental crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCreation. 0aGiftsxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aHuman ecologyxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079149402840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791494028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791494028/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles